The official currency of the Falkland Islands is the Falkland Islands Pound (FKP), whose value is set at the value of one British pound (GBP).
Money can be exchanged at the only bank on the islands located in Stanley opposite the FIC West.
In general, British Pounds are accepted everywhere on the islands, and within Stanley, and credit cards and US dollars are also often accepted.
On the outlying islands, credit cards are unlikely to be used, although British and US currencies may be used; ask owners in advance to know which payment method is accepted.
It is virtually impossible to exchange Falkland currency outside the islands, so make sure to exchange your money before leaving the islands.
